{"word":"ἐπήβολος","slug":"ἐπήβολος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπήβολος</b></el> <el>(ἐπή-βολος, ον) (<a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> for <el>ἐπί-βολος</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπιβάλλω'><el>ἐπιβάλλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>having achieved</i> or <i>gained</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>ἐπ. φρενῶν</el> <i>compos mentis</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>pertaining to, befitting</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}